## 1. System Overview & User Roles

This is a **multi-store Cloth ERP system** with two main roles:

| Role | Access | Portal URL |
|------|--------|------------|
| **Admin** | Everything — Masters, Purchase, Dispatch, Reports, Settings | `/admin/...` |
| **Store Staff** | Sales, Inventory view, Returns | `/staff/...` |

**Login URLs:**
- Admin: `https://your-app.vercel.app/login/admin`
- Staff: `https://your-app.vercel.app/login/staff`

---

## 2. Step 1 — Initial Setup (Settings)

> **Complete this before using any other module.**

### 📍 Go to: Settings

### 2.1 Company Profile
- Fill in your **company name**, address, GSTIN, logo.
- This appears on all printed invoices.

### 2.2 Create Users
- Go to **Settings → Users**.
- Click **Add User** to create store staff accounts.
- Assign each user a **role** (Admin/Staff) and a **store**.

### 2.3 Configure Number Series
- Go to **Settings → Number Series**.
- Define prefix/format for: Purchase Bills, Sale Invoices, Dispatch Notes, etc.
- Example: `INV-2026-0001`

### 2.4 Set Preferences
- Go to **Settings → Preferences**.
- Enable/disable features: Loyalty Points, GST, Barcode printing, etc.

### 2.5 Configure GST
- Go to **GST → Tax Rates**.
- Add GST slabs: 0%, 5%, 12%, 18%, 28%.
- These are linked to items during product creation.

---

## 3. Step 2 — Master Data

> **Masters are reference data. Set them up before creating items or transactions.**

### 📍 Go to: Masters

| Master | What it does |
|--------|-------------|
| **Suppliers** | Companies from which you buy cloth/products |
| **Customers** | Retail customers (can earn loyalty points) |
| **Stores (Warehouses)** | Your physical store locations |
| **Categories** | Product categories (e.g., Shirts, Trousers, Sarees) |
| **Brands** | Product brands |
| **Salesmen** | Staff who assist in sales |
| **Banks** | Your bank accounts (for financial entries) |

### How to add a Supplier:
1. Go to **Masters → Suppliers** → Click **Add Supplier**.
2. Fill in: Name, Contact Person, Phone, Address, GSTIN.
3. Click **Save**.

---

## 4. Step 3 — Item / Product Management

> **Items = the individual products (with variants like size & color).**

### 📍 Go to: Items

### 4.1 Add a New Item
1. Click **New Item**.
2. Fill in:
   - **Item Name** (e.g., "Men's Formal Shirt")
   - **SKU / Barcode**
   - **Category** (select from Masters)
   - **Brand** (select from Masters)
   - **GST Slab** (select %)
   - **Sale Price / Cost Price**
   - **Size, Color**
3. Click **Save**.

### 4.2 Barcode
- After saving, the system generates a barcode.
- You can **print barcodes** from Items or after a Purchase.

> 💡 **Tip:** Each size-color combination is a separate product (variant) in the system.

---

## 5. Step 4 — Purchase (Stock Inward)

> **When you receive goods from a supplier, create a Purchase Bill.**

### 📍 Go to: Purchase → Purchase Bills

### 5.1 Create a Purchase Bill
1. Click **Add Purchase**.
2. Select:
   - **Supplier** (from Masters)
   - **Warehouse** (which store/godown receives the stock)
   - **Invoice Number** & **Invoice Date** (from supplier's bill)
3. **Add Items**: Search for product variants, set quantity & rate.
4. Optionally add **Other Charges**.
5. Click **Save Bill**.

### What happens automatically:
- ✅ Stock increases for the selected warehouse.
- ✅ GST is calculated per item's tax slab.
- ✅ A Ledger entry (Accounts Payable) is created.
- ✅ A purchase number is auto-generated (e.g., `PUR-2026-000001`).

### 5.2 Print Barcodes After Purchase
- From the Purchase Bills list, click the **🖨️ Barcode** icon.
- Select items and quantities, then print barcode labels.

### 5.3 View / Cancel Purchase
- Click **👁️ View** to see full bill details.
- Click **✎ Edit** to modify (if not completed).
- To reverse: contact admin (cancel purchase reverses stock and ledger).

---

## 6. Step 5 — Dispatch (Factory → Store)

> **Transfer stock from the central factory/godown to a store branch.**

### 📍 Go to: Inventory → Transfer

### 6.1 Create a Dispatch
1. Click **New Transfer**.
2. Select **Source Store** (factory/godown) and **Destination Store**.
3. Search and add products with quantities.
4. Click **Dispatch**.

### What happens automatically:
- ✅ Stock decreases from source store.
- ✅ Stock increases at destination store.
- ✅ A Dispatch Note is created (with date and number).

---

## 7. Step 6 — Inventory Management

### 📍 Go to: Inventory

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Stock Overview** | View current stock levels across all stores |
| **Stock Transfer** | Move stock between stores |
| **Stock Adjustment** | Correct stock manually (for count differences) |
| **Stock Audit** | Run an audit and reconcile stock |
| **Movement History** | View all stock in/out movements for any product |

### How to check stock:
1. Go to **Inventory → Stock Overview**.
2. Filter by **Store** or **Category**.
3. Items with low stock are highlighted in red.

---

## 8. Step 7 — Pricing & Schemes

### 📍 Go to: Pricing

#### 8.1 Price Lists
- Create custom **price lists** for specific stores or periods.
- Useful when one store has different pricing than others.
- Go to **Pricing → Price Lists** → **New Price List**.
- Add item-specific prices and assign the list to a store.

#### 8.2 Discount Schemes
- Go to **Pricing → Schemes** → **New Scheme**.
- Types of schemes:
  - **Flat discount** (e.g., 10% off all items)
  - **Buy X Get Y** (e.g., Buy 2 get 1 free)
  - **Amount threshold** (e.g., 15% off on bills above ₹2,000)
- Set **validity dates** and assign to specific stores.

#### 8.3 Coupons
- Go to **Pricing → Coupons**.
- Create coupon codes customers can use at billing.
- Set discount amount/%, usage limit, and expiry.

---

## 9. Step 8 — Sales (POS Billing)

> **Core daily activity — creating invoices when a customer buys products.**

### 📍 Go to: Sales → New Sale

### 9.1 Create a Sale Invoice
1. Click **New Sale**.
2. **Select Store** (the billing store).
3. **Search Customer** (or leave as Walk-in Customer).
4. **Add Items**: Scan barcode or search by name/SKU.
   - Each item shows price, quantity, and applied price.
5. **Apply Discounts**:
   - Select an active **Scheme** (auto-applied if eligible).
   - Enter a **Coupon Code**.
   - Redeem **Loyalty Points** (if customer has points).
6. Select **Payment Mode**: Cash / Card / UPI.
7. Click **Complete Sale**.

### What happens automatically:
- ✅ Store inventory decreases for sold items.
- ✅ Invoice is generated with a sale number.
- ✅ Customer earns loyalty points (if configured).
- ✅ Ledger entry is posted (Sales + Cash/Bank).
- ✅ GST is calculated on the sale.

### 9.2 View Sales History
- Go to **Sales → Sales Invoices**.
- Filter by date, customer, or payment status.
- Click **👁️ View** to see full invoice details.

---

## 10. Step 9 — Customer Rewards

### 📍 Go to: Customer Rewards

#### 10.1 Loyalty Points
- Go to **Customer Rewards → Loyalty Config**.
- Set how many points a customer earns per ₹ spent.
- Set how much 1 point is worth in discount (e.g., 100 points = ₹10 off).
- Points are earned automatically on every sale.
- Points are redeemed at the time of billing.

#### 10.2 Customer View
- Go to **Customer Rewards → Rewards**.
- Search a customer to view their full **loyalty transaction history**.
- See total earned, redeemed, and balance points.

#### 10.3 Gift Vouchers
- Go to **Customer Rewards → Gift Vouchers**.
- Click **Issue Voucher** to create a voucher with a fixed value.
- The customer can redeem it on a future purchase.

#### 10.4 Credit Notes
- Issued when a customer returns goods and wants store credit instead of a refund.
- Applied to their next purchase automatically.
- View at **Customer Rewards → Credit Notes**.

---

## 11. Step 10 — Returns

### 📍 Returns are handled from the Purchase and Sales sections

#### 11.1 Purchase Return (Supplier Return)
1. Go to **Purchase → Purchase Bills**.
2. Click the **↩ Return** icon on the relevant bill.
3. Select items and quantities to return.
4. Click **Submit Return**.
5. Stock decreases, and payable is reduced.

#### 11.2 Sales Return (Customer Return)
1. Go to **Sales → Sales Invoices**.
2. Click the **↩ Return** icon on the relevant invoice.
3. Select items and quantities being returned.
4. Choose if refund goes as **cash** or **credit note**.
5. Click **Submit Return**.
6. Stock increases back into the store.

---

## 12. Step 11 — Accounts & Finance

### 📍 Go to: Accounts (Sidebar under Reports/Settings)

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Overview** | View all account balances |
| **Bank Payment** | Record a payment made from bank |
| **Bank Receipt** | Record a payment received into bank |
| **Ledger** | View full debit/credit history for any account |

> **Note:** Most entries are created automatically from Purchase, Sales, and Returns. Manual entries are for bank transfers, expenses, etc.

---

## 13. Step 12 — GST

### 📍 Go to: GST

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Tax Rates** | Manage GST slabs (0%, 5%, 12%, 18%, 28%) |
| **Invoice Tax Report** | View tax collected on all sales invoices |
| **GSTR Summary** | Monthly GST summary for filing returns |

### GST Workflow:
1. ✅ Create GST slabs in **GST → Tax Rates**.
2. ✅ Assign slabs to products when creating items.
3. ✅ System auto-calculates CGST/SGST/IGST on each sale.
4. ✅ View summary in **GST → GSTR Summary** for filing.

---

## 14. Step 13 — Reports

### 📍 Go to: Reports

| Report | What it shows |
|--------|--------------|
| **Sales Report** | All sales with filters by date, store, product, salesman |
| **Purchase Report** | All purchases with supplier and item breakdown |
| **Stock Report** | Current stock across all stores with value |
| **Ledger Report** | Account-wise transaction history |
| **Profit Analysis** | Revenue vs Cost, gross margin per product |
| **Collection Report** | Daily/weekly cash and bank collections |
| **Customer Report** | Customer-wise purchase history and loyalty stats |
| **Vendor Report** | Supplier-wise purchase history |
| **Movement Report** | Product stock movement in/out over time |
| **Age Analysis** | How long stock has been sitting (identify dead stock) |
| **Bank Book** | Bank account transaction register |

### Exporting Reports:
- Each report has an **Export** button (📥).
- Reports can be exported as **Excel/CSV**.

---

## 15. Quick Reference: Daily Workflow

```
MORNING
  ✅ Login as Admin/Staff
  ✅ Check Stock Overview (Inventory)
  ✅ Check low-stock alerts

DURING THE DAY
  ✅ Create Sales (POS Billing)
  ✅ Apply coupons/schemes at billing
  ✅ Handle returns (if any)

WHEN STOCK ARRIVES
  ✅ Create Purchase Bill (with supplier invoice)
  ✅ Print barcodes for new stock
  ✅ Transfer stock to stores via Dispatch

END OF DAY
  ✅ View Collection Report (daily cash)
  ✅ Verify Sales Report totals
  ✅ Check Accounts for any pending entries

MONTHLY
  ✅ Generate GSTR Summary for GST filing
  ✅ Review Profit Analysis Report
  ✅ Run Stock Audit for accuracy
```

---

